The '''Embassy of Ireland in Japan''' ({{lang-ga|Ambasáid na hÉireann, An tSeapáin}}) is the [[diplomatic mission]] of the [[Republic of Ireland]] in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/japan/about-us/the-embassy/|title=The Embassy - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|last=Affairs|first=Department of Foreign|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref>

The current{{when|date=November 2018}} ambassador to Japan is Paul Kavanagh,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/IrishEmbJapan/status/1062590472173031424|title=アイルランド大使館 Ireland in Japan on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en}}</ref> who had previously served as the Irish Ambassador to the United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/government-finalises-new-ambassador-appointments-1.3519396|title=Government finalises new ambassador appointments|work=The Irish Times|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en-US}}</ref>

The embassy is also represented by an [[Consul (representative)|Honorary Consul]] in [[Sapporo]], [[Hokkaido]] prefecture.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/embassies/irish-embassies-abroad/asia-and-oceania/japan/|title=Japan - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|last=Affairs|first=Department of Foreign|website=www.dfa.ie|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref>

