{{Infobox journal | title = Philosophy | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Philosophy <!-- ISO 4 abbreviation --> | bluebook = <!-- For law journals only --> | discipline = <!-- or |subject= --> | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = <!-- or |editors= --> | publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] for the [[Royal Institute of Philosophy]] | country = United Kingdom | history = 1926 to present | frequency = | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0031-8191 | eISSN = 1469-817X | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayJournal?jid=PHI | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
'''''Philosophy''''' is the [[academic journal|scholarly journal]] of the [[Royal Institute of Philosophy]]. It is designed to be intelligible to the non-specialist reader and has been in continuous publication for almost 90 years. It is published by [[Cambridge University Press]] and is currently [[Editor-in-chief|edited]] by [[Anthony O'Hear]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.royalinstitutephilosophy.org/page/33 |title=Royal Institute Philosophy |publisher=Royal Institute Philosophy |date= |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>
The journal was established in 1926 "to build bridges between specialist philosophers and a wider educated public." Each issue contains a "New Books" section and an editorial on a topic of philosophical or public interest.<ref name=cambridge>{{cite web|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayJournal?jid=PHI |title=Philosophy - Cambridge Journals Online |publisher=Journals.cambridge.org |date= |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>
