The '''Sheikh Mukhtar-Vali Complex''' is a [[mausoleum]] located 5 km southwest of the town of [[Yangiariq]], [[Xorazm Region]], [[Uzbekistan]]. It was erected in the 16th century, above the grave of [[Sheikh Mukhtar-Vali]].

This site was added to the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage]] Tentative List on 1 June 1996.<ref>UNESCO World Heritage Centre [http://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/798/ "Complex of Sheikh Mukhtar-Vali (mausoleum)"] Retrieved 15 July 2009.</ref>

